Issue: Desktop runtime treated validated progress writeback as ordinary agent resume.

Symptom:
- RUN-20260709-173840383Z completed with round_result=continue and validation_valid=true.
- Worker reports created/validated spec and pending artifacts, and loop_handoff.next_prompt explicitly requested ledger writeback.
- activity.json still had ledger_stage.status=not_ready, writeback_required=false, ledger_write_result=null.
- Desktop therefore exposed Resume instead of Write Ledger.

Evidence:
- /Users/Glare/Library/Application Support/Electron/runtime/runs/RUN-20260709-173840383Z/result.json had changed_files under arckit/spec and arckit/pending.
- The same result had source_projection_check.source_facts_changed and artifact_ownership_scan.pending_items populated.
- The controller review intentionally kept loop_handoff.status=continue because the case could not close.
- agent-orchestrator previously made ledger_stage gate_ready only when loop_gate.status=done.
- gate-engine previously rejected every non-done round_result and blocked any non-empty blocked_projections.
- ledger-writer previously advanced the selected dimension to target_state and removed the selected gap on every accepted writeback.

Conclusion:
- The runtime conflated "loop can close" with "validated progress should be written".
- A continue round can require ledger writeback before the next agent round, without closing the active case or selected gap.

Fix:
- agent-orchestrator now marks continue rounds with resolved report intake and source/pending/ledger-owned changes as ledger_stage=gate_ready/writeback_required=true.
- gate-engine now allows continue progress writeback when ledger_stage is gate_ready and report intake is resolved.
- blocked_projections remain warnings for progress writeback; they still block final done writeback.
- ledger-writer now distinguishes final vs progress writeback. Progress writeback records evidence and case progress without advancing the selected dimension to target_state or removing the selected gap.
- Desktop automatic gate detection and renderer controls now treat ledger_stage=gate_ready/writeback_required=true as Write Ledger, even when round_result=continue.

Verification:
- npm run check passed in runtime/arckit-runtime.
- validate-result passed against RUN-20260709-173840383Z/result.json.
- In-memory patched RUN-20260709-173840383Z with ledger_stage=gate_ready allowed evaluateRuntimeGates with only a warning about unresolved blocked_projections.
- writeLedger dry-run with the patched result produced an allowed plan and wrote no files.
- npm run smoke passed in runtime/arckit-runtime.

Temporary instrumentation:
- No runtime debug console or trace markers were added.
